    <body>
      <pb n="1"/>
      <p>(The (bad) Hebrew of this letter is as follows):–</p>
      <p rend="indent(1)">And now my friend and beloved,<lb/> very secretly I shall reveal to you
        that<lb/> many of my friends advise me to go to<lb/>
        <placeName>San Francisco</placeName>. Since for many years past<lb/> you have given me clear
        proof that you<lb/> love me as a brother. Write to me <del>from the</del><lb/> very
        seriously about this matter. Many<lb/> people tell me that it will be a great<lb/> thing for
        a man like me, and that, un–<lb/>doubtedly, I will be able to support my<lb/> household. I
        hope you will reply quickly,<lb/> for if I write to those people about this<lb/> matter, I
        shall reveal my plan to the<lb/> directors of the school, since, in any<lb/> event, I am
        compelled to tell<lb/> them about it. My friend, the Chazan,<lb/> who works with me, keeps
        on telling<lb/> me to write, and that, undoubtedly, they<lb/> will receive me with open
        arms. I await<lb/> your reply and shall act according<lb/> to your advice. Your everlasting friend,<lb/>
        <persName role="author">Simon–Noht</persName></p>
      <p>P.S. Undoubtedly I'll be able to transact business three<lb/> for there is merchandise in
        plenty, especially of the Ashke–<lb/>nazic Minhag; such as Hebrew books, prayer shawls
        of<lb/> all kinds.</p>
    </body>
  </text>
